<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc00d21d5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s16325"><num value="16325">§ 16325.</num><heading> Science and Technology Scholarship Program</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idc00d21d6-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s16325/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary is authorized to establish a Science and Technology Scholarship Program to award scholarships to individuals that is designed to recruit and prepare students for careers in the Department and National Laboratories.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idc00d21d7-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s16325/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Service requirement</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may require that an individual receiving a scholarship under this section serve as a full-time employee of the Department or a National Laboratory for a fixed period in return for receiving the scholarship.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idc00d21d8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/58/tIX/s984A">Pub. L. 109–58, title IX, § 984A</ref>, <date date="2005-08-08">Aug. 8, 2005</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/119/908">119 Stat. 908</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
